stories.storyText:
[Code Name] Utage
[Gender] Female
[Combat Experience] None
[Place of Birth] Higashi
[Date of Birth] April 4
[Race] Unknown
[Height] 161cm
[Infection Status] 
Confirmed infected by medical examination.

[Physical Strength] Normal
[Mobility] Normal
[Physical Resilience] Normal
[Tactical Acumen] Normal
[Combat Skill] Excellent
[Originium Arts Assimilation] Normal

An ordinary student from Higashi who came to study in Lungmen, Utage contracted Oripathy after getting pulled into an incident with Infected persons. After coming to Rhodes Island per physician's advice, Utage passed the evaluation to become an Operator.
She is level-headed in her view of Oripathy, living life largely the same as before she became Infected. However, when she is working, she exhibits a terrifying demeanor.

Imaging tests reveal blurry outlines of this operator's internal organs, clouded with abnormal dark spots. Her circulatory system shows an abnormally high rate of Originium particulate matter, with other signs of Oripathy infection, we can confirm that the Operator is Infected. 

[Cell-Originium Assimilation] 2%
Operator Utage is Infected, but has no external signs of infection.

[Blood Originium-Crystal Density] 0.18u/L
Operator Utage rarely comes in contact with Originium. Please maintain that situation.

This exchange student from Higashi loves to eat, chases the latest fashion trends, and likes to have a good time. After contracting Oripathy after getting caught up in an incident, she came to Rhodes Island in accordance with her physician's advice. At first, a non-combat role was planned for her based upon her complete lack of combat experience, but during the evaluation, she demonstrated a considerable talent for fighting. After some discussion, the examiner decided to let her participate in some field missions. Of course, the bulk of her work will still be non-combat related, such as logistics or HR work more suitable for someone her age.

Utage revels in the challenge of new things. As fashion is constantly shifting and lines up with her interests, she naturally pays more attention to these things. Over time, she has become a bit of an authority. What company is gearing up to release a new product, and how does its prospects on the market look? She always has her finger on the pulse of new information, and is ready to share it with any nearby Operators who are interested. Thanks to her, the average fashionability of the Operators here has improved greatly, but their wallets have been proportionally flattened.

I must note that Utage is very good at disguising and manipulating her mental state. As a result, conventional psychological monitoring methods are not reliable in her case. In addition to her strong psychological qualities, I also believe that her race has something to do with the phenomenon. The other Operators from Higashi have no insights as to her race, and unless she decides to disclose this information herself, we might have to commit a lot of effort into this question... Wait, you mean, her blade? Hmm.... perhaps there is a lot we can learn from her blade. This line of tracking may well be more successful than other alternatives. Understood, I'll get in touch with Vulcan. Once I have the information, I'll enter it into the database and make it available to you.

'You're back? Did you get it done? I see. Still couldn't find anything, huh? Guess that's not unexpected... Hey, s-stop hitting me, it's my bad, so stop already!'
'I know you had good intentions and wanted the Doctor to get to know each Operator better. However, everyone has their own secrets, right? For example, you wouldn't want everyone to find out right now that you're planning to propose to your girlfriend and have an engagement ring in a compartment in your desk. Oh, how'd I find out? Well, uh, ahahaha.'
'What's important is not to air out every nitty gritty detail about an Operator's life, but rather to determine whether or not they are trustworthy, and assign them accordingly. That's already enough. Utage deserves the Doctor's trust, as well as ours, but she may never decide to trust us with her secrets. As for the Doctor, perhaps she will eventually open up, given the right time and place.

[Excerpts from an Encrypted Channel - Regarding Utage] 
'If you want to know what's 'in' with the chicks, then you've come to the right place.'
'She's really good at creating a laid-back atmosphere.'

'She always has her finger on the pulse. Whenever something limited edition hits the market, she's on top of it right away. Being able to strike a business deal was super lucky.'

'D-did she just give me an evil eye? I could feel shivers going down my spine...'

'I can't figure out what that kid is thinking.'

'When she smiles like that, yes, those vibes, now that's a bit interesting.'

'That's just me faking it~ I don't mind teach you if you want to learn.'

An outfit commonly worn by Operators.
While not as practical as a uniform, it's what they find most comfortable.

An outfit that has been improved after the Operator's Promotion.
Custom-made to suit each Operator's experiences and needs, these outfits are designed to provide them maximum flexibility on any battlefield. Furthermore, this is all done without compromising the comfort that they've come to expect.

modules.desc:
Operator Utage has demonstrated a remarkable aptitude for solo confrontation with the enemy while far removed from support lines.
The Field Operations Department has thus passed the following resolution:
This operator shall be appointed a Guard Operator during field operations to exercise Musha responsibilities.
In witness whereof,
This badge is hereby conferred upon the above named.

[♥ Case Lily Nail Salon] Dear customers, our new location is now open! We've imported a state-of-the-art Colombian nail printer. Come give it a try! Make an appointment so you won't have to wait. Mwah~!
[Bank Alert] Your bank card payment failed due to insufficient funds.
[♥ Case Lily Nail Salon] Dear customer, your appointment on March 22nd was cancelled because we didn't receive your deposit. Please book with us again. Mwah~!
[Lungmen Report] This week's Munchventure takes us to a donburi restaurant located in the shopping district. The taste-to-price ratio is through the roof, so the place is always packed. Whew, look at that tender, juicy meat. Gulp it up and feel your troubles wash away.
Our adventurers paint a picture of the restaurant's owner, one Mr. Matsumoto, as a young, successful, and overall admirable entrepreneur. When we asked about his plans for the future, the shy young man blushed and told us he was ready to give up being single and hoped to enjoy a café date with his special someone. We wish him well.
[Large Hot Coffee] Autumn is coming, enjoy a cup of coffee with it. Your 'drink voucher' is about to expire. You'll want to come get your voucher set ASAP!
[Large Hot Coffee] Your autumn latte is done and your delivery is on the way to Case Lily Nail Salon.
[Eat Your Heart Out] Wow, you'll never guess who I saw today at the donburi restaurant. The woman who owns the nail salon! It turns out she's been in every day lately! Wasn't she trying to lose weight?!
[Flowers For Love] The bouquet you ordered has been delivered to the donburi restaurant at 1455 Busy Street, and received by the owner. At your service, delivering Flowers For Love♬.
[Beauty Makeover] Guess who I saw today while getting my nails done. Matsumoto from the donburi restaurant! He even brought coffee for the boss! They must be an item!
[Lungmen Report] This week, we visit the donburi restaurant in the shopping district again. Their new menu incorporates all kinds of cuteness for the ladies. Check out that pink heart on top, it's too adorable to eat!
[♥ Case Lily Nail Salon] Dear customers, the owner of our salon recently got engaged. In celebration, we have discounts on various styles, and you can enjoy even deeper discounts by booking in advance. Come give us a try, new friends and old. Mwah~!

voice_lines.voiceText: Doctor, ready to get to work? I won't take no for an answer! C'mon! 3, 2, 1, start!
Nails are part of a girl's appeal. Gotta take care of them properly.
Why do I call myself Utage? Well, it's not that complicated. I just want to be happy as if we were throwing a party every night. As long as I'm in a good mood, everything else is gonna be okay.
You already saw it, Doctor? Well, that's too bad... C'mon, let's use up this two-person discount coupon.

When I contracted Oripathy and was to be sent here, my mother was afraid I'd be bullied, and gave me the family heirloom, Shishiou, to defend myself with. Didn't find any bullies, but I did manage to cut some pretty nasty folks. Doctor, you really know how to appeal to people.
Everyone here gets pretty scary when they get serious. I'm as scary as six people combined? Am I really that terrifying...?

Help me pick up ten boxes of limited-edition cookie sticks tomorrow? Just take the money out of my account. Huh? Preorders are already sold out? Then... c'mon, you've gotta think of a way, Doctor! Please!
Doctor, you're razor-sharp some of the time and dull as a piece of wood at others. I don't get why. Oh, I see, right out of 'Flirting Guidebook,' huh? I'd expect nothing less from you, Doctor.
It's not good to rely too much on any single person, but I'll make an exception for... Eek, Doctor! Oh it's nothing, I was just rambling to myself! D-d-did you need anything from me?
If you're tired, just go to bed. Not that complicated.
Hey, Doctor. I'm the Operator who just joined recently, Utage. My interests are... Oh, I don't need to go into the details? In that case, I look forward to working with you.
Is it over?
Do I get to do less work if I get promoted? No dice? Oh well...
It's time to move out. Let's crush those nasty folks~
All right everyone, I'll be counting on your orders!
I'm the team leader? ...Eh? Me? Team leader?
Let's go.
C'mon, c'mon! I can't wait any longer.
Mhmm.
Need me?
Moving out~
Hehe.
Who should I cut?
It won't hurt if I don't miss.
Just send me the leftover parts.
You look rather cute when you're crying.
Ahh, I'm finally done blowing off steam, how exciting. Doctor, let's get some crepes.
How exciting. Thanks for all the support~
You're saving the stragglers for me? Well, I'll dig right in.
Doctor, stop spacing out and start running.
As long as I can buy the new magazines, it doesn't really matter where I'm staying.
Hmm?
Let's go sing karaoke?
Arknights.
Oh hey, Doctor. As you can see, I've been abducted by this kotatsu. Wanna hop in together? It's really warm. C'mon, give it a try, I promise you won't regret it~
Good morning to you, Doctor.

Doctor, happy birthday. Did you know? There's a real trick to birthday parties. I could share some hacks with you, like, on the down-low, to really up your popularity at dinnertime. Number one— wait, are these all your presents?! This whole room?!

The dinner party today was, like, killer. That's the kind of thing you should really do every day. Otherwise, you start overthinking things and get all hung up on it. Then stuff gets worse and lose all your optimism for life, which is tough to hold onto. Meh, that's just me babbling to myself, don't worry about it. Anyway, enjoy the happiness you've got in the moment, that's what matters most!
